      <abstract>
        <p>Diphenylmethane-based compounds bearing heterocyclic recognition groups, capable to act as hydrogen bonding sites were established to be powerful receptors for carbohydrates. In this paper, we describe the synthesis of a further representative of this class of compounds, containing four 1,8-naphthyridine groups as recognition units. The title compound has been characterized by elemental analysis, <sup>1</sup>H-NMR, <sup>13</sup>C-NMR and mass spectrometry.</p>
      </abstract>
